<h1 id="getters-and-setters">Getters and setters</h1>
<p>Apart from function shorthands, you can define special attributes that do something when read or set.</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">Shop = {
  get closed () {
    return this.status === 'closed'
  },
  set closed (value) {
    this.status = value ? 'closed' : 'open'
  }
}

Shop.closed = true  // invokes `set closed()`
Shop.status         //=&gt; 'closed'
Shop.closed         //=&gt; true (invokes `get closed()`)
</code></pre>
<ul>
<li></li>
</ul>
